WEBVTT

00:00:24.654 --> 00:00:30.403
because I understand and appreciate
the power of place.

00:00:30.427 --> 00:00:34.848
Now, Madison called his estate Montpelier.

00:00:34.872 --> 00:00:37.570
And Montpelier is absolutely beautiful.

00:00:37.594 --> 00:00:41.348
It's several thousand acres
of rolling hills,

00:00:41.372 --> 00:00:43.476
farmland and forest,

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:48.269
with absolutely breathtaking views
of the Blue Ridge Mountains.

00:00:48.619 --> 00:00:50.419
But it's a haunting beauty,

00:00:51.244 --> 00:00:57.013
because Montpelier
was also a slave labor camp.

00:00:57.720 --> 00:01:00.976
You see, James Madison enslaved
more than 100 people